BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 430.86 Tm (11.1 What It Is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 412.70 Tm (RDS Proxy is a managed database proxy that sits between your application and RDS/Aurora.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 390.84 Tm (11.2 Why It Exists) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 368.68 Tm (Problem: Lambda + RDS = connection explosion) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 356.80 Tm (  Each Lambda invocation opens a new DB connection) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 344.92 Tm (  100 concurrent Lambdas = 100 connections) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 333.04 Tm (  RDS has connection limits \(varies by instance size\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 321.16 Tm (  Result: connection exhaustion, errors) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 309.28 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 297.40 Tm (Solution: RDS Proxy) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 285.52 Tm (  Proxy maintains a connection pool to the database) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 273.64 Tm (  Lambda connects to proxy \(fast, reuses connections\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 261.76 Tm (  Proxy multiplexes to actual DB connections) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 237.88 Tm (11.3 Benefits) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 219.72 Tm (- Connection pooling: reduces DB connection pressure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 205.86 Tm (- Failover handling: faster failover, app doesn't need reconnect logic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 192.00 Tm (- IAM authentication: integrate with IRSA/IAM for credential-free access) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 178.14 Tm (- TLS enforcement: can enforce encrypted connections) Tj ET
