BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 448.38 Tm (Trap 1) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 430.22 Tm ("IAM is for app user login.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 414.36 Tm (Correct:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 398.50 Tm (Usually no. IAM governs AWS identities and permissions. Cognito handles end-user) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 384.64 Tm (authentication for apps.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 362.78 Tm (Trap 2) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 344.62 Tm ("SQS guarantees exactly once.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 328.76 Tm (Correct:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 312.90 Tm (Standard queues are at-least-once. Design idempotent consumers.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 291.04 Tm (Trap 3) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 272.88 Tm ("SNS replaces queues.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 257.02 Tm (Correct:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 241.16 Tm (SNS is fan-out pub/sub. It does not replace durable per-consumer buffering the way SQS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 227.30 Tm (does.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 205.44 Tm (Trap 4) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 187.28 Tm ("EventBridge is just another queue.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 171.42 Tm (Correct:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 155.56 Tm (It is an event-routing bus, not a simple queue.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 133.70 Tm (Trap 5) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 115.54 Tm ("Encryption at rest means only KMS exists.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 99.68 Tm (Correct:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 83.82 Tm (KMS manages keys and integrates with services. The end-to-end security story includes IAM,) Tj ET
