BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 668.84 Tm (5. 25 High-Value Interview Q&As) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 641.04 Tm (1. When would you choose ECS over EKS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 622.88 Tm (Choose ECS when the main requirement is running containers on AWS with lower operational) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 609.02 Tm (complexity. Choose EKS when Kubernetes APIs, tooling, portability, or platform) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 595.16 Tm (standardization matter enough to justify the added operational burden.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 573.30 Tm (2. What is the difference between Multi-AZ and read replicas in RDS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 555.14 Tm (Multi-AZ is primarily for high availability and failover. Read replicas are primarily for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 541.28 Tm (read scaling and offloading read traffic.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 519.42 Tm (3. Why use private subnets for application servers?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 501.26 Tm (Private subnets reduce direct exposure to the internet. Public traffic should terminate at) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 487.40 Tm (controlled entry points such as ALB or API Gateway, while app servers stay reachable only) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 473.54 Tm (through internal paths.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 451.68 Tm (4. When would Lambda be a poor choice?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 433.52 Tm (For long-running, stateful, low-latency-sensitive, or highly predictable heavy-throughput) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 419.66 Tm (workloads where container or instance-based compute is operationally and economically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 405.80 Tm (better.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 383.94 Tm (5. What is the difference between ALB and NLB?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 365.78 Tm (ALB is Layer 7 and supports HTTP-aware routing such as host/path rules. NLB is Layer 4 and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 351.92 Tm (is better for TCP/UDP, very high performance, and certain static-IP use cases.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 330.06 Tm (6. Why is S3 not suitable as a database?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 311.90 Tm (S3 is object storage, not a transactional query engine. It lacks relational semantics,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 298.04 Tm (low-latency row-level updates, and database-style indexing/query behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 276.18 Tm (7. When do you choose DynamoDB over RDS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 258.02 Tm (When access patterns are known, scale is very high, low-latency key-based access matters,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 244.16 Tm (and relational joins are not central to the problem.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 222.30 Tm (8. What is the danger of a bad DynamoDB partition key?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 204.14 Tm (It creates hot partitions, uneven traffic distribution, throttling, and poor scale) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 190.28 Tm (behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 168.42 Tm (9. Why use ElastiCache?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 150.26 Tm (To reduce database read pressure, improve latency for hot data, and absorb bursty traffic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 136.40 Tm (It should complement, not replace, good data modeling.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 114.54 Tm (10. What does least privilege mean in IAM?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 96.38 Tm (Grant only the minimum actions on the minimum resources required for a principal to do its) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 82.52 Tm (job, and nothing more.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 479.00 24.00 Tm (Page 48 of 147) Tj ET
endstream
