BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 790.00 Tm (11. Why are IAM roles preferred over access keys?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 771.84 Tm (Roles avoid hardcoded long-lived credentials, improve rotation posture, and fit AWS's) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 757.98 Tm (temporary-credential model for workloads.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 736.12 Tm (12. What is envelope encryption in KMS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 717.96 Tm (Data is encrypted with a data key, and the data key is encrypted with a KMS-managed master) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 704.10 Tm (key. This scales better than using a master key directly for all data operations.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 682.24 Tm (13. What problem does SQS solve?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 664.08 Tm (It decouples producers and consumers, buffers spikes, improves resilience, and allows) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 650.22 Tm (asynchronous processing.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 628.36 Tm (14. Why must SQS consumers be idempotent?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 610.20 Tm (Because standard SQS provides at-least-once delivery, so duplicates can occur and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 596.34 Tm (consumer must handle them safely.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 574.48 Tm (15. When is SNS plus SQS a strong pattern?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 556.32 Tm (When one event must fan out to multiple independent consumers and each consumer needs) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 542.46 Tm (isolated retry and failure handling.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 520.60 Tm (16. When is EventBridge better than SNS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 502.44 Tm (When event routing depends on event content or you want an event-bus model with rule-based) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 488.58 Tm (dispatch to multiple targets.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 466.72 Tm (17. When should Step Functions be used?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 448.56 Tm (When the workflow has multiple steps, branching, retries, compensation, or long-running) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 434.70 Tm (orchestration that should be explicit rather than buried inside application code.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 412.84 Tm (18. How do you design a secure file-upload system on AWS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 394.68 Tm (Use Cognito or your auth layer for identity, issue pre-signed S3 URLs, keep the bucket) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 380.82 Tm (private, encrypt with KMS-backed settings, store metadata separately, and serve downloads) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 366.96 Tm (through controlled access such as CloudFront if needed.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 345.10 Tm (19. How would you make a web application highly available in one region?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 326.94 Tm (Deploy compute across multiple AZs behind a load balancer, keep databases in Multi-AZ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 313.08 Tm (mode, store static assets in S3, use health checks and autoscaling, and avoid) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 299.22 Tm (single-instance dependencies.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 277.36 Tm (20. What would you monitor for a production API?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 259.20 Tm (Latency, error rate, throughput, saturation metrics, downstream dependency health, queue) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 245.34 Tm (depth, and key business metrics.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 223.48 Tm (21. What is a good rollback strategy for production deployments?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 205.32 Tm (Use immutable artifacts, health checks, deployment stages like canary or blue-green where) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 191.46 Tm (risk justifies it, and automatic or manual rollback triggered by verified failure signals.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 169.60 Tm (22. Why is Infrastructure as Code important?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 151.44 Tm (It makes infrastructure reproducible, reviewable, versioned, and less prone to manual) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 137.58 Tm (drift or undocumented changes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 115.72 Tm (23. How would you reduce AWS cost without harming reliability?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 97.56 Tm (Right-size compute, use Savings Plans or Reserved capacity where stable, use Spot for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 83.70 Tm (fault-tolerant workloads, optimize storage classes, remove idle resources, and cache or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 69.84 Tm (tune before brute-force scaling.) Tj ET
