BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 382.84 Tm (For a React SPA, there are two common models:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 360.98 Tm (Model A: Static Hosting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 344.80 Tm (- build React into static assets) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 330.94 Tm (- upload to S3) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 317.08 Tm (- serve through CloudFront) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 303.22 Tm (This is usually the best model for a normal SPA.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 281.36 Tm (Model B: Frontend Container) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 265.18 Tm (- build React app) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 251.32 Tm (- copy static output into Nginx image) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 237.46 Tm (- run that container on EC2, ECS, or EKS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 223.60 Tm (This is valid if:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 207.74 Tm (- the organization wants everything in containers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 193.88 Tm (- frontend is SSR or has server logic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 180.02 Tm (- deployment model is standardized around containers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 166.16 Tm (For a plain React SPA, static hosting is usually simpler and cheaper.) Tj ET
