BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 576.04 Tm (6.2 Internet Gateway - The Front Door) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 557.88 Tm (The Internet Gateway \(IGW\) is attached to your VPC. It allows resources in public subnets) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 544.02 Tm (to communicate with the internet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 528.16 Tm (Real-life analogy:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 508.30 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 496.42 Tm (IGW = the main entrance of your building.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 484.54 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 472.66 Tm (If your room \(subnet\) has a hallway to the main entrance  -> public subnet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 460.78 Tm (If your room has NO hallway to the main entrance          -> private subnet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 442.90 Tm (Important:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 427.04 Tm (- the IGW itself does not cost money) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 413.18 Tm (- it does not limit bandwidth significantly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 399.32 Tm (- you need exactly one per VPC) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 385.46 Tm (- it is the reason your ALB can receive internet traffic) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 365.60 Tm (6.3 ALB - The Smart Receptionist) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 347.44 Tm (The Application Load Balancer sits in public subnets and is the entry point for HTTP/HTTPS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 333.58 Tm (traffic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 317.72 Tm (What it does:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 297.86 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 285.98 Tm (1. Receives requests from the internet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 274.10 Tm (2. Terminates TLS \(handles HTTPS certificates\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 262.22 Tm (3. Reads the HTTP request \(path, headers, host\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 250.34 Tm (4. Routes to the right backend based on rules:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 238.46 Tm (     /api/*     -> Spring Boot service) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 226.58 Tm (     /admin/*   -> Admin service) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 214.70 Tm (     /health    -> Health check service) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 202.82 Tm (5. Only sends traffic to healthy targets) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 190.94 Tm (6. Distributes load across multiple instances/tasks/pods) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 173.06 Tm (Real-life analogy:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 153.20 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
