BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 790.00 Tm (You might think: "Why not just put Spring Boot in a public subnet and skip the ALB?") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 774.14 Tm (Reasons:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 754.28 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 742.40 Tm (1. Direct exposure -> any attacker can probe your app directly) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 730.52 Tm (2. No load balancing -> one instance = single point of failure) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 718.64 Tm (3. No health checks -> broken instance still receives traffic) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 706.76 Tm (4. No TLS termination -> each instance manages certificates) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 694.88 Tm (5. No routing rules -> cannot split traffic by path) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 683.00 Tm (6. No connection draining during deploys) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 671.12 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 659.24 Tm (The ALB is not optional overhead. It is a critical safety and operations layer.) Tj ET
0.6 w 46.00 635.36 m 549.00 635.36 l S
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 605.36 Tm (7. How Your Backend Reaches the Outside World) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 583.56 Tm (Your backend sits in a private subnet. It cannot reach the internet by default. But) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 569.70 Tm (sometimes it needs to:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 553.84 Tm (- call external APIs \(Stripe, Twilio, email providers\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 539.98 Tm (- download packages during setup) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 526.12 Tm (- pull container images) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 64.00 512.26 Tm (- reach AWS services that are outside the VPC) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 492.40 Tm (7.1 NAT Gateway - The Outbound-Only Door) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 474.24 Tm (NAT = Network Address Translation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 458.38 Tm (Real-life analogy:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 438.52 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 426.64 Tm (Imagine your office building has a security rule:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 414.76 Tm (  "People outside cannot walk in uninvited.") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 402.88 Tm (  "But people inside CAN walk out, do their errands, and come back.") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 391.00 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 379.12 Tm (The NAT Gateway is that one-way exit door.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 367.24 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 355.36 Tm (  Outbound: allowed \(your backend can call Stripe\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 343.48 Tm (  Inbound:  blocked \(Stripe cannot randomly connect to your backend\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 325.60 Tm (How it works:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 305.74 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 293.86 Tm (Spring Boot \(private subnet, IP: 10.0.10.15\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 281.98 Tm (      |) Tj ET
