BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 398.46 Tm (13. Interview-Ready Answers) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 370.66 Tm (13.1 "How does a user's request reach your Spring Boot backend on AWS?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 348.50 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 336.62 Tm ("The user's browser resolves the API domain via Route 53, which points to ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 324.74 Tm (an ALB in a public subnet. The ALB terminates TLS, evaluates routing rules, ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 312.86 Tm (and forwards the request to a healthy Spring Boot instance in a private ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 300.98 Tm (subnet. The backend processes the request, queries RDS in another private ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 289.10 Tm (subnet, and sends the response back through the ALB.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 265.22 Tm (13.2 "Why private subnets for the backend?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 243.06 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 231.18 Tm ("Private subnets have no route to the Internet Gateway, so they cannot be ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 219.30 Tm (directly reached from the internet. This reduces attack surface. The ALB ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 207.42 Tm (in the public subnet acts as the controlled entry point. Backend instances ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 195.54 Tm (only accept traffic from the ALB's security group.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 171.66 Tm (13.3 "How does your backend in a private subnet call external APIs?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 149.50 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 137.62 Tm ("Through a NAT Gateway in a public subnet. The private subnet's route table ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 125.74 Tm (sends 0.0.0.0/0 traffic to the NAT Gateway, which translates the private IP ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 113.86 Tm (to a public IP for outbound requests. Inbound internet traffic is still ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 101.98 Tm (blocked. For AWS service calls like S3 or Secrets Manager, I use VPC ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 90.10 Tm (endpoints to keep traffic private and avoid NAT costs.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 66.22 Tm (13.4 "Explain security groups in your architecture") Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 479.00 24.00 Tm (Page 96 of 147) Tj ET
