BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 786.00 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 774.12 Tm ("Each layer has its own security group. The ALB allows inbound HTTPS from ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 762.24 Tm (the internet. The backend allows inbound on port 8080 only from the ALB's ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 750.36 Tm (security group. The database allows inbound on port 5432 only from the ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 738.48 Tm (backend's security group. This creates a chain where each layer only ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 726.60 Tm (accepts traffic from the layer directly above it. No layer is directly ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 714.72 Tm (exposed beyond its intended purpose.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 690.84 Tm (13.5 "What is the difference between Internet Gateway and NAT Gateway?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 668.68 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 656.80 Tm ("Internet Gateway allows two-way internet traffic for public subnets - ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 644.92 Tm (both inbound and outbound. It is used by ALBs and anything that needs ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 633.04 Tm (to be publicly reachable.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 621.16 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 609.28 Tm (NAT Gateway allows one-way outbound internet access for private subnets. ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 597.40 Tm (Resources behind it can reach the internet, but the internet cannot ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 585.52 Tm (initiate connections to them. I use it when the backend needs to call ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 573.64 Tm (external APIs like payment gateways.") Tj ET
0.6 w 46.00 549.76 m 549.00 549.76 l S
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 519.76 Tm (14. Quick Revision Sheet) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 491.96 Tm (Every Component in One Line) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 469.80 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 457.92 Tm (VPC            = your private network on AWS) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 446.04 Tm (Subnet         = a slice of the VPC in one AZ, public or private) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 434.16 Tm (Internet GW    = the front door for public internet access \(two-way\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 422.28 Tm (NAT Gateway    = the back door for private subnet outbound-only internet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 410.40 Tm (Route Table    = the map that says "traffic to X goes through Y") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 398.52 Tm (Security Group = per-resource firewall \(bouncer at each door\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 386.64 Tm (NACL           = per-subnet firewall \(security gate per floor\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 374.76 Tm (ALB            = HTTPS load balancer and smart router \(receptionist\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 362.88 Tm (Route 53       = DNS service \(phone directory\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 351.00 Tm (CloudFront     = CDN \(branch offices serving copies worldwide\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 339.12 Tm (VPC Endpoint   = private shortcut to AWS services, skips internet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 327.24 Tm (ACM            = free TLS certificates for your domains) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 303.36 Tm (The Standard 3-Tier Network Layout) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 281.20 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 269.32 Tm (Public Subnet:   ALB, NAT Gateway) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 257.44 Tm (Private Subnet:  Backend compute \(EC2, ECS, EKS\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 245.56 Tm (Private Subnet:  Database \(RDS, ElastiCache\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 221.68 Tm (Traffic Flow Cheat Sheet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 199.52 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 187.64 Tm (User -> App:        Route 53 -> CloudFront -> S3) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 175.76 Tm (User -> API:        Route 53 -> ALB \(public\) -> Backend \(private\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 163.88 Tm (Backend -> DB:      Private subnet -> Private subnet \(via security group\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 152.00 Tm (Backend -> Redis:   Private subnet -> Private subnet \(via security group\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 140.12 Tm (Backend -> S3:      VPC Gateway Endpoint \(free, private\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 128.24 Tm (Backend -> Stripe:  NAT Gateway -> Internet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 116.36 Tm (Backend -> Secrets: VPC Interface Endpoint \(private\) or NAT Gateway) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 92.48 Tm (Gold Standard Sentence) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 70.32 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 479.00 24.00 Tm (Page 97 of 147) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
