BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 790.00 Tm ("On AWS, I place the ALB in public subnets as the only internet-facing ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 778.12 Tm (entry point. The backend runs in private subnets, reachable only through the ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 766.24 Tm (ALB. The database sits in private subnets, reachable only from the backend. ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 754.36 Tm (Outbound internet access uses a NAT Gateway, and AWS service calls use VPC ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 742.48 Tm (endpoints to stay private and save costs. Security groups enforce least-privilege ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 730.60 Tm (at every layer, and Route 53 handles DNS for both external users and internal ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 718.72 Tm (service discovery.") Tj ET
0.6 w 46.00 694.84 m 549.00 694.84 l S
