BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 778.00 Tm (14.2 "Where would you store user uploaded files?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 755.84 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 743.96 Tm ("I would store the actual files in S3 and keep metadata in a database) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 732.08 Tm (like RDS. For uploads, I prefer pre-signed URLs so the browser can upload) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 720.20 Tm (directly to S3 without routing large file traffic through the backend.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 696.32 Tm (14.3 "When would you use EBS vs EFS vs S3?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 674.16 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 662.28 Tm ("I use EBS when one machine needs a disk, like an EC2 root volume.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 650.40 Tm (I use EFS when multiple machines need a shared filesystem with mounted) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 638.52 Tm (file semantics. I use S3 for object storage like assets, documents,) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 626.64 Tm (backups, and uploads. For most application files, S3 is the default.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 614.76 Tm (EFS is only when shared filesystem semantics are genuinely required.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 590.88 Tm (14.4 "When RDS vs DynamoDB?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 568.72 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 556.84 Tm ("I choose RDS when the data is relational and I need transactions,) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 544.96 Tm (joins, and flexible SQL queries. I choose DynamoDB when access patterns) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 533.08 Tm (are known up front and the workload fits key-value or document access) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 521.20 Tm (at large scale with low-latency reads and writes. For a typical Spring) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 509.32 Tm (Boot business app with users, orders, and payments, I would usually start) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 497.44 Tm (with RDS.") Tj ET
