BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 780.00 Tm (4. Story Mode: Your App Grows Up) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 752.20 Tm (Phase 1: "We just deployed, it works") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 734.04 Tm (The team puts Spring Boot on EC2, PostgreSQL on RDS.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 718.18 Tm (They hardcode the DB password in application.yml. They use the default security group that) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 704.32 Tm (allows all traffic. There is no HTTPS.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 688.46 Tm (This works. It is also completely insecure.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 666.60 Tm (Phase 2: "Security review said we have problems") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 648.44 Tm (Someone audits the setup and finds:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 628.58 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 616.70 Tm (Problem 1: DB password is in the source code repo) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 604.82 Tm (Problem 2: RDS is reachable from the internet) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 592.94 Tm (Problem 3: No TLS - API traffic is unencrypted) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 581.06 Tm (Problem 4: EC2 instance has admin-level AWS permissions) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 569.18 Tm (Problem 5: No user authentication on the API) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 551.30 Tm (Now the team starts fixing things.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 529.44 Tm (Phase 3: "We locked it down properly") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 511.28 Tm (After fixing:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 491.42 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 479.54 Tm ([ok] DB password in Secrets Manager, injected at runtime) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 467.66 Tm ([ok] RDS in private subnet, security group allows only backend) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 455.78 Tm ([ok] ALB terminates HTTPS with ACM certificate) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 443.90 Tm ([ok] EC2/ECS uses scoped IAM role with least privilege) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 432.02 Tm ([ok] API validates JWT tokens from Cognito or custom auth) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 420.14 Tm ([ok] S3 buckets are private with block public access) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 408.26 Tm ([ok] EBS and RDS volumes encrypted with KMS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 390.38 Tm (That is the journey. Let us walk through each layer.) Tj ET
