BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 479.68 Tm (13.1 "How do you handle secrets in your application?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 457.52 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 445.64 Tm ("I store all secrets - database credentials, API keys, JWT signing keys - ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 433.76 Tm (in AWS Secrets Manager. The application reads them at startup using the ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 421.88 Tm (AWS SDK, authorized by its IAM task role. No secrets are hardcoded, stored ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 410.00 Tm (in environment files, or baked into Docker images. For ECS, I use the ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 398.12 Tm (secrets field in the task definition so ECS injects them as environment ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 386.24 Tm (variables from Secrets Manager directly.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 362.36 Tm (13.2 "How do you implement least privilege?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 340.20 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 328.32 Tm ("Every service gets its own IAM role scoped to exactly the actions and ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 316.44 Tm (resources it needs. The Spring Boot backend might have ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 304.56 Tm (s3:GetObject/PutObject on the uploads bucket and ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 292.68 Tm (secretsmanager:GetSecretValue on its own secrets. No wildcard actions, ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 280.80 Tm (no wildcard resources. On EKS, I use IRSA so each pod gets its own ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 268.92 Tm (IAM identity. On ECS, each service gets its own task role.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 245.04 Tm (13.3 "How does your app authenticate users?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 222.88 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 211.00 Tm ("I use Cognito User Pools for user registration and login. Cognito issues ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 199.12 Tm (JWT tokens. The React frontend includes the token in every API request. ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 187.24 Tm (Spring Security validates the JWT signature using Cognito's JWKS endpoint, ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 175.36 Tm (checks expiration, and extracts user identity. Authorization is handled ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 163.48 Tm (at the controller level with role-based access and at the service level ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 151.60 Tm (with data ownership checks.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 127.72 Tm (13.4 "How is data encrypted?") Tj ET
