BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 790.00 Tm (For regulated workloads, I use customer-managed KMS keys for audit trail ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 778.12 Tm (and key rotation control.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 754.24 Tm (13.5 "What is the difference between IAM and Cognito?") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 732.08 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 720.20 Tm ("IAM controls which AWS services and resources your infrastructure and ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 708.32 Tm (applications can access. Cognito controls who your end users are and ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 696.44 Tm (issues them tokens. IAM is for machine-to-service authorization. ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 684.56 Tm (Cognito is for human-to-application authentication. They serve ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 672.68 Tm (completely different layers.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 648.80 Tm (13.6 "Walk me through the security of a single API request") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 626.64 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 614.76 Tm ("The request arrives at the ALB over HTTPS, so it is encrypted in transit.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 602.88 Tm (The ALB is in a public subnet; the backend and database are in private ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 591.00 Tm (subnets. The ALB forwards to the backend, which validates the JWT token ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 579.12 Tm (issued by Cognito. The backend queries RDS over a TLS connection, using ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 567.24 Tm (credentials from Secrets Manager that it has permission to access via ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 555.36 Tm (its IAM task role. The response returns through the same encrypted path.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 543.48 Tm (Network access is enforced by security groups at every layer, and IAM ) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 531.60 Tm (ensures the backend can only touch the specific AWS resources it needs.") Tj ET
0.6 w 46.00 507.72 m 549.00 507.72 l S
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 477.72 Tm (14. Quick Revision Sheet) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 449.92 Tm (The Four Security Layers) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 427.76 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 415.88 Tm (IAM              = what can my code touch in AWS?) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 404.00 Tm (Network          = what traffic can flow where?) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 392.12 Tm (Secrets + Crypto = how are credentials and data protected?) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 380.24 Tm (App Auth         = who are my users and what can they do?) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 356.36 Tm (One-Line Mapping) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 334.20 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 322.32 Tm (IAM Role            = badge that lets your app call AWS services) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 310.44 Tm (Security Group      = bouncer at each resource's door) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 298.56 Tm (Secrets Manager     = locked safe for passwords and API keys) Tj ET
