BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 790.00 Tm () Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 772.12 Tm (What makes this good:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 752.26 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 740.38 Tm (1. User gets fast response \(sync part is only validate + charge + save\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 728.50 Tm (2. Downstream work is decoupled \(each consumer independent\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 716.62 Tm (3. Failures are isolated \(email failure does not block inventory\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 704.74 Tm (4. Adding a new consumer is easy \(subscribe new queue to topic\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 692.86 Tm (5. Everything is observable \(CloudWatch metrics, logs, alarms\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 680.98 Tm (6. Failed messages are not lost \(DLQ catches them\)) Tj ET
0.6 w 46.00 657.10 m 549.00 657.10 l S
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 627.10 Tm (14. Common Mistakes and Debugging Tips) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 599.30 Tm (14.1 "We do everything synchronously") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 577.14 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 565.26 Tm (Problem: one slow downstream call makes the entire API slow.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 553.38 Tm (Fix: move non-critical work to queues.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 541.50 Tm (Ask: "Does the user need this result right now?" If no -> queue it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 517.62 Tm (14.2 "Our SQS consumer is not idempotent") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 495.46 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 483.58 Tm (Problem: duplicate messages cause duplicate charges or emails.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 471.70 Tm (Fix: check if the message was already processed before executing business logic.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 459.82 Tm (Use: order_id as idempotency key, stored in DB.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 435.94 Tm (14.3 "We have no DLQ") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 413.78 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 401.90 Tm (Problem: one bad message blocks the queue forever.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 390.02 Tm (Fix: configure DLQ with maxReceiveCount \(e.g., 3\).) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 378.14 Tm (Monitor: alarm on DLQ message count > 0.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 354.26 Tm (14.4 "We use Lambda for everything including our main API") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 332.10 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 320.22 Tm (Problem: Java Lambda cold starts are 5-15 seconds. Users see spinners.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 308.34 Tm (Fix: use Lambda for event-driven background tasks.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 296.46 Tm (Use ECS/EKS for the main Spring Boot API.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 272.58 Tm (14.5 "We have no alarms") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 250.42 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 238.54 Tm (Problem: you find out about outages from users, not from monitoring.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 226.66 Tm (Fix: at minimum, alarm on ALB 5xx, SQS queue depth, DLQ messages, Lambda errors.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 202.78 Tm (14.6 "Our SNS subscriber is down and messages are lost") Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 180.62 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 168.74 Tm (Problem: SNS pushes to an endpoint that is down. Message is gone.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 156.86 Tm (Fix: never subscribe a direct HTTP endpoint to SNS for critical flows.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 144.98 Tm (Instead: SNS -> SQS -> consumer. SQS stores messages until consumer is ready.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 46.00 121.10 Tm (14.7 Quick Debug Mental Model) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 98.94 Tm ([text]) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 87.06 Tm (Message not arriving at consumer?) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 75.18 Tm (  1. Is the producer actually sending? \(check CloudWatch metrics or logs\)) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 58.00 63.30 Tm (  2. Is the SQS queue receiving? \(check ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 479.00 24.00 Tm (Page 145 of 147) Tj ET
endstream
